  <!-- ============ SECTION IV — RULES ============ -->
  <section>
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="section-num">§ IV.</div>
      <h2>Universal Rules</h2>
      <div class="section-tag">always</div>
    </div>

    <ol class="rules-list">
      <li>Always spray product onto the cloth — <strong>never directly onto the instrument</strong>.</li>
      <li><strong>Detailing applies, Suede buffs.</strong> Keep them separate at all times.</li>
      <li>Use separate cloths by purpose: strings, body, polish. <strong>Never cross-contaminate.</strong></li>
      <li>Paper barrier between strings and fretboard when using Fast Fret on the <strong>Mayones</strong>.</li>
      <li>Stop Fast Fret entirely if you switch to <strong>coated strings</strong> (Elixir, D'Addario XT).</li>
      <li>The after-session dry wipe handles <strong>80% of instrument care</strong>. Less is more.</li>
      <li>No liquids near the SLB100 electronics — <strong>piezo, jack, preamp area</strong>.</li>
      <li>Strings off before applying F-One Oil. Wash cloths separately, no fabric softener.</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

